    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "What is inference.sh and how does it work?",
        "answer": "inference.sh is a cloud platform that hosts over 250 AI applications. You use a CLI tool to send requests to these applications and receive results. No GPU or local infrastructure is required."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do I authenticate with the inference.sh CLI?",
        "answer": "Run infsh login to authenticate through a browser. For automated environments, set the INFSH_API_KEY environment variable with your API key."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I use local files with AI applications?",
        "answer": "Yes. The CLI automatically uploads local files when you provide a file path instead of a URL. Any field that accepts a URL also accepts a local path."
      },
      {
        "question": "What AI models are available?",
        "answer": "The platform offers image models like FLUX and Gemini, video models like Veo and Seedance, language models including Claude and Gemini through OpenRouter, search tools like Tavily and Exa, and Twitter automation utilities."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do I track long-running tasks?",
        "answer": "Submit tasks with the --no-wait flag to return immediately. Use infsh task get task-id to check status and retrieve results when the task completes."
      },
      {
        "question": "Are there specialized skills for specific AI tasks?",
        "answer": "Yes. Specialized skills are available for image generation, video generation, language models, web search, avatar videos, and Twitter automation. Install them with npx skills add inference-sh/skills at skill-name."
      }
    ]
